A Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) has been signed  between ARTICLE 19 and the National Human Rights Commission (NHRC), Bangladeshfor mutual  collaboration with the project;
o	A high level national consultant, Mr. Kazi Reazul Hoque, Immediate-past Chairman of NHRC has been commissioned as Advisor for the project to facilitate  the joint activities;
o	Developed  a charter for women journalists for their safety and protection of those who exercise FoE;
o	Organized 1 highlight events on World Press Freedom day focusing on impunity, safety and protection issues.

o	Monitored and documented cases of violation of freedom of expression  and reporting through public and media statements, gathered data to use in Annual State of Freedom of Expression in Bangladesh; 
o	An online portal for women journalists s (Kannashahoshini) has been launched (http://kanyasahosini.com/) 
o	Reviewed and adapted  protocols for Emergency Safety Protection programme, Shohojogita;
